<section>
	<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 overflow-hidden">
		<div class="py-12 md:py-20">
			<div class="py-4 sm:py-6 lg:py-8">
				<div class="flex flex-wrap md:-mx-8">
					<div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 px-0 sm:px-8">
						<div class="mb-12 lg:mb-0 pb-12 lg:pb-0 border-b lg:border-b-0">
							<h2 class="mb-8 text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold font-heading">
								Core Principles
							</h2>

							<p class="mb-8 text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
								Privacy by Architecture means designing your system, or homelab, so that tools and data run on your own hardware. 
								Your machine becomes the center of your network, not a node in someone elseâ€™s cloud.
							</p>
							<p class="mb-8 text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
								Autonomy is the antidote to the invisible strings of social engineering baked into proprietary tools. 
								By building on open-source foundations, you own the process and the output, pure utility, designed for creative mastery.
							</p>


						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 px-0 sm:px-8">
						<ul class="space-y-12">
